Dear [1]gun registry petition signer:

Wednesday afternoon April 28th, the[2] Public Safety and Security Committee
again will discuss the witness list for Candice Hoeppner's bill to end the
wasteful long-gun registry, Bill C-391.

Widespread media reports insist that Liberal MP Mark Holland's proposed witness
list is very short on supporters of Bill C-391. Conservative MP Brent
Rathgeber, who also sits on the committee, [3]specifically says Holland wants
to deny the Canadian Taxpayers Federation (CTF) an opportunity to appear as a
witness.

The CTF has every reason to appear before this committee. We speak on behalf of
thousands of supporters and have a long [4]history of advocacy on the gun
registry. Besides, in the interests of democracy and fairness, witnesses should
reflect both sides of the gun registry debate, not just one.

[5]Click here to email Liberal, BQ and NDP committee members asking them to
invite the CTF as a witness. Otherwise, cut and paste these addresses:

[6]Davies.D@parl.gc.ca, [7]MenarSe@parl.gc.ca, [8]HollaM@parl.gc.ca,
[9]Kania.A@parl.gc.ca, [10]MouraMa@parl.gc.ca, [11]Oliphant.R@parl.gc.ca

As well, this week's CTV online poll asks, "Do you support the long gun
registry?" [12]Click here to respond.

The time is short. Let's make our voices heard!

--Kevin, Troy, Lee, and the rest of the CTF team

The Canadian Taxpayers Federation is funded solely by taxpayers who believe in
its mandate of lower taxes, less waste, and more accountable government.
